I"•<h2 id="background">Background</h2>
<p>This application is the result of my homework topic in the CTU Implementation of User Interfaces course.</p>

<h3 id="installation--setup">Installation &amp; Setup</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Create an account on <a href="https://developer.riotgames.com/">Riot Developer Portal</a> and generate your DEVELOPMENT API KEY.</li>
  <li>In the API folder, replace the text in Key.txt with your key. Donâ€™t worry, .gitignore already contains this file.</li>
  <li>Build and run the application.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="application-overview">Application overview</h3>
<p>This applicationâ€™s primary purpose is to look up a summoner and show his data, like his Teamfight Tactics profile and match history, in a user-friendly way.
It uses REST to get data from RiotAPI and is implemented in C#. As it is a WPF application, it follows the MVVM design pattern.</p>

